						<summary>

						<p>The beginning of this inscription is damaged and it is left incomplete towards the end. It records a gift of 75 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning two perpetual lamps inside the central shrine of the temple with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee for each lamp, by one Kumaraṉ Sarvadēvaṉ of Dēvanūr who had already presented two hanging lamps to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
